C_1, C_2, C_3, C_4
\mid C_1\mid = \mid C_2\mid = 1
a \in A
C_3
(x,y) \in \rho
a
(a=x, a=y, a=x=y
\left|\left\{ \left(x,y\right)\in\rho\mid x=a\right\} \right|=\left|\left\{ \left(x,y\right)\in\rho\mid y=a\right\} \right|=|C_3|
\left|\left\{ \left(x,y\right)\in\rho\mid x=a\right\} \cap\left\{ \left(x,y\right)\in\rho\mid y=a\right\} \right|=\left|\left\{ a,a\right\} \right|=1
\left|\left\{ \left(x,y\right)\in\rho\mid x=a\vee y=a\right\} \right|=2|C_3|-1
P=\left\{ \left(x,y\right)\in\rho\mid x=a\right\} 
Q=\left\{ \left(x,y\right)\in\rho\mid y=a\right\} 
\left|P\cup Q\right|
P\cap Q=\left\{ \left(a,a\right)\right\} 
\left|P\cap Q\right|=1
\left(x,y\right)\in P\iff x=a\wedge y\in C_{3}
\left|P\right|=\left|C_{3}\right|
P=\{a\}\times C_3
\left(x,y\right)\in Q\iff x\in C_{3}\wedge y=a
\left|Q\right|=\left|C_{3}\right|
Q=C_3\times\{a\}
\left|P\cup Q\right|=\left|P\right|+\left|Q\right|-\left|P\cap Q\right|=\left|C_{3}\right|+\left|C_{3}\right|-1=2\left|C_{3}\right|-1
2*(|C3|-1)+1 = 2*|C3|-1
